Turkey Authorities Consider New Steps to Tame Demand, Sabah Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-05-20T05:17:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/turkey-authorities-consider-new-steps-to-tame-demand-sabah-says.html
Turkey may place limits on credit
card borrowing and other loans after June 12 elections in a bid
to limit the current-account deficit, Sabah newspaper reported.  Authorities are considering steps that would tie credit
card borrowing limits to income levels, and higher transaction
charges on bank loans, the newspaper said, without saying how it
got the information.  The  Finance Ministry  is also considering higher  import
taxes  and raising the levy on luxury items, it said. The central
bank may raise reserve requirements for banks further, it said.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
